# Final Year Project (FYP): Extending LaZer with a Module-LWE Public-Key Encryption Module

## Overview
This repository contains our final-year project work built on top of the LaZer cryptographic library.
Our current focus is the implementation of a reusable Module-LWE public-key encryption (PKE) module using LaZer’s algebra primitives, together with testing, benchmarking, and Python demo support.  


## Relationship to LaZer
This project is built on top of the LaZer cryptographic library.
The original LaZer codebase serves as the upstream foundation, while our FYP work extends it with additional scheme-layer functionality.

## Our main contributions
- `src/public_key_encryption/` — core Module-LWE PKE implementation
- `python/public_key_encryption/` — Python wrapper and demo scripts for PKE
- `Makefile.pke` — dedicated build support for PKE-related components

## Where to look first
For our main FYP contributions, start with:
- `src/public_key_encryption/`
- `python/public_key_encryption/`
- `Makefile.pke`

## Where to look first
For our main FYP contributions, start with:
