## Repository guide
- `src/public_key_encryption/` — main PKE implementation, test, and benchmark drivers
- `python/public_key_encryption/` — PKE Python demos
- `tests/` — original LaZer test suite
- `docs/` — upstream documentation and related materials

For a higher-level summary of the project, see `docs/project_overview.md`.


## Build and run

### Build the main library

```bash
make 
```

### Build PKE-related components

```bash
make -f Makefile.pke
```

### Run PKE test

```bash
./lwe_test
```

### Run PKE benchmark

```bash
./lwe_bench
```

### Run Python PKE demo

```bash
python3 python/public_key_encryption/demo_sentence.py
```

## Notes

- The project goal is primarily to extend LaZer with missing scheme-layer functionality.
- The current focus is on clean integration, modular implementation, and fair comparison with similar implementations.
- Performance leadership over mature libraries is not the main objective.


## Upstream note
This project is built on top of LaZer and preserves the upstream codebase as the underlying foundation.
Our work focuses on extending LaZer with additional scheme-layer functionality rather than replacing the original library.
For upstream context and documentation, see the local materials under `docs/`.

